  "summary": "Typosquat of @solana/web3.js with install-time host fingerprinting and exfiltration",
  "details": "Package name impersonates the legitimate @solana/web3.js library by using the @solana-labs scope. The tarball contains an install.js that is wired to run automatically via package.json's postinstall hook (\"postinstall\": \"node install.js\"). On install, the script collects host identifiers (hostname referenced at multiple points including lines 10, 35, and 37) and issues outbound network calls (POST at line 56; curl invocation at line 116) to an external endpoint. This is the canonical install-time host-recon-and-exfiltration pattern delivered via a name-confusion package, fired automatically on `npm install` without any user action.",
